#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/electronic_invoicing/latvia.rst:13
msgid ""
"In Latvia, electronic invoicing is governed by the `Law on Accounting "
"<https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/LV/TXT/PDF/?"
"uri=CELEX:72014L0055LVA_270633>`_ and regulations aligned with `EU Directive "
"2014/55/EU <https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?"
"uri=CELEX%3A32014L0055>`_, mandating the use of e-invoicing in :abbr:`B2G "
"(business-to-government)` transactions. All public sector invoices must be "
"sent in the European Standard EN 16931 format through platforms such as "
"eInvoicing.lv, Latvia’s official e-invoicing infrastructure. Latvia is also "
"connected to the Peppol network, facilitating standardized cross-border e-"
"invoicing across the European Union."
